title: EcoTrack: A Personal Carbon Footprint Tracker
skills_required: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Python, : CSV/JSON or Firebase/MongoDB , Google Maps API , UI/UX Design (basic level), Git & GitHub
overview: EcoTrack is a web-based tool that helps individuals monitor their daily carbon footprint based on travel, energy use, and consumption habits. Users can input daily activities such as vehicle usage, electricity consumption, diet choices, and more. The application then provides insights and suggestions to reduce their environmental impact over time.

title: FitTrack: A Personal Fitness and Health Tracker
skills_required: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Python (Flask or Django), Node.js, SQLite or Firebase, Nutritionix API, Google Fit API, React Native or Flutter, UI/UX Design (basic level), Git & GitHub
overview: FitTrack is a mobile and web application designed to help users track their daily fitness activities, calorie intake, sleep patterns, and overall health goals. It provides personalized workout routines, meal plans, and progress tracking to help users stay motivated and achieve their health goals. The app will generate insights based on user inputs and suggest ways to improve overall fitness.

title: SkillSwap: A Peer-to-Peer Skill Exchange Platform
skills_required: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (React or Vue.js), Python (Flask or Django), or Node.js, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, or Firebase,
overview: SkillSwap is a web platform that connects individuals who want to learn new skills with others willing to teach them. Users can list the skills they offer (e.g., guitar, coding, cooking) and the skills they wish to learn. The platform helps match users based on availability, location (optional), and interest, encouraging a barter-based learning ecosystem without monetary exchange.
